    "chunk_id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2001_Solutions_2001s_page_002_16",
    "text": "Note: Richard Stanley points out a theorem of Ryser (see Ryser, Combinatorial Mathematics, Theorem 3.1) that can also be applied. Namely, if A and B are 0 I matrices with the same row and column sums, then there is a sequence of operations on 2 x 2 matrices of the form",
